y\":\"Q\",\"green_key\":\"P\",\"correctCount\":8,\"total_n_questions\":11,\"quiz_passed\":true},{\"rt\":273171,\"response\":{\"strategy\":\"Better of finding out where the red squares are likely to be as early as possible.\\n\\nTo do this I looked at the punk squares and picked the first shift based on how many pink squares the first shift would pass over. But I thought of this strategy well into the second city.\\n\\nSometimes to reduce risk I went with the 'L' shapes routes that would have equal horizontal and vertical squares on the route. This was especially true in cities where I couldn't determine if the city had column or row fees.\"},\"trial_type\":\"survey-text\",\"trial_index\":379,\"time_elapsed\":2095530,\"internal_node_id\":\"0.0-328.0\",\"final_zoom_factor\":0.684870188003581,\"blue_key\":\"Q\",\"green_key\":\"P\",\"correctCount\":8,\"total_n_questions\":11,\"quiz_passed\":true},{\"rt\":101154,\"response\":{\"observations\":\"If I could grasp early on what the city was, I would make decisions accordingly. Sometimes I did take big risks depending on what the routes presented.\\n\\nIf I could work out the the city early then that made decisions easier.\"},\"trial_type\":\"survey-text\",\"trial_index\":380,\"time_elapsed\":2196685,\"internal_node_id\":\"0.0-329.0\",\"final_zoom_factor\":0.684870188003581,\"blue_key\":\"Q\",\"green_key\":\"P\",\"correctCount\":8,\"total_n_questions\":11,\"quiz_passed\":true},{\"rt\":39526,\"response\":{\"lookahead\":\"From City 2 onwards, I paid careful attention to the pink squares right at the start. These squares would determine which option I take for the first shift of the day.\"},\"trial_type\":\"survey-text\",\"trial_index\":381,\"time_elapsed\":2236213,\"internal_node_id\":\"0.0-330.0\",\"final_zoom_factor\":0.684870188003581,\"blue_key\":\"Q\",\"green_key\":\"P\",\"correctCount\":8,\"total_n_questions\":11,\"quiz_passed\":true},{\"rt\":19244,\"response\":{\"other_comments\":\"If this is it, it was a nice and short